## Scaffolding hygiene

- **Gitignore new tooling artefacts in the same PR that introduces the tool.**
  When scaffolding a new dependency, audit what the tool writes to disk on
  first use and add those paths to `.gitignore` *before* opening the PR.
  Common leaks by stack:
  - **TypeScript / tsc -b:** `*.tsbuildinfo`
  - **Node frameworks:** `.next/`, `.turbo/`, `.nuxt/`, `.svelte-kit/`, `.vite/`
  - **Bundlers / packers:** `dist/`, `build/`, `out/`
  - **Mobile (Capacitor / RN):** `ios/App/App/public/`, `ios/Pods/`,
    `ios/build/`, `android/build/`, `android/.gradle/`, `android/app/build/`,
    `DerivedData/`, `capacitor.config.json` (copies generated by `cap sync`)
  - **Python:** `__pycache__/`, `.pytest_cache/`, `.mypy_cache/`,
    `.ruff_cache/`, `*.egg-info/`
  - **Rust:** `target/`
  - **Java / JVM:** `.gradle/`, `build/`, `out/`, `*.class`
  - **Go:** test binaries (`*.test`), `coverage.out`
  - **Editors:** `.idea/`, `.vscode/` (unless intentionally shared),
    `.DS_Store`, `Thumbs.db`
  Avoids per-task follow-up commits cleaning up leaked artefacts, which
  was a recurring noise source on early tasks.

